  "prompt": "What's a good uninstalled for windows?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a reliable **uninstaller** for Windows that can thoroughly remove programs, including leftover files, registry entries, and traces, here are some popular and effective options:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Revo Uninstaller**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Advanced scanning for leftovers (files, folders, and registry entries).  \n  - Forced uninstall for stubborn programs.  \n  - Includes additional tools like startup manager, browser cleaner, and junk remover.  \n  - Free and paid versions available.  \n\n---\n\n### **2. IObit Uninstaller**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Batch uninstallation for multiple programs.  \n  - Powerful scanning for leftover files and registry entries.  \n  - Browser extension removal and software health monitoring.  \n  - Free and pro versions available.  \n\n---\n\n### **3. Geek Uninstaller**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Simple and lightweight interface.  \n  - Force removal for stubborn programs.  \n  - Thorough scan for leftovers (files and registry entries).  \n  - Freeware with a portable version available.  \n\n---\n\n### **4. Ashampoo UnInstaller**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Real-time installation monitoring for complete removal.  \n  - Snapshots to compare system before and after installations.  \n  - Includes cleaning tools for system optimization.  \n  - Paid software with a free trial.  \n\n---\n\n### **5. BCUninstaller**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Open-source and free.  \n  - Batch uninstallation and forceful removal.  \n  - Simple and lightweight interface.  \n\n---\n\n### **6. Wise Program Uninstaller**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Free and easy to use.  \n  - Force removal for stubborn programs.  \n  - Scanning for leftovers.  \n  - Portable version available.  \n\n---\n\n### **7. CCleaner (with Uninstaller Feature)**  \n- **Key Features**:  \n  - Built-in uninstaller with the ability to scan for leftovers.  \n  - Includes system cleaning and optimization tools.  \n  - Free and paid versions available.  \n\n---\n\n### **Recommendation**:  \nFor most users, **Revo Uninstaller** or **IObit Uninstaller** are excellent choices due to their thoroughness and additional features. If you prefer something lightweight and free, **Geek Uninstaller** or **BCUninstaller** are great alternatives. Always download from official websites to avoid malware.",
